Anyway I decided to post seperate as I think there is a bigger non flame issue at hand. And that is the eq drinal market in general. I am not crazy on the drinal market, frankly even as a n00b i enjoyed the MM market much better, sure the times where different, but on MM when naggy/vox was still a pretty respectable accomplishment youwould still see CoF and RBB's and white scale cloaks for sell lin nfp, and only hte people in the very high end uber guilds could afford them. On drinal you dont see too much high end game (by today's standards) being sold. How often have you seen a swift blade of zek for sell? How often have you seen a Yelnak earring for sell? These are just 2 examples of some high end gear (by today's standards) you dont see for sale on our server. <br>
<br>
Now this isnt a flame on the server or anything like that. What I do want to stress to the server and to the peopel who frequent these boards is that the cunsomer sets a value of a item. Not too many days ago I saw someone offering to pay 200k for a mana robe. Now granted a mana robe is a extremely rare drop of a tough mob or whateber, but this person will get his mana robe and the next person seling a mana robe will prolly want to 200k-ish for his/her robe. Another example is a fungi. Before the drop nerf they where going for what? 30-35 on average? Now what they go for 40ish? Peopel are paying 5-10more k for  a item that has been aruond for about as long as kunark has? Regardless of how rare it maybe now (i never camped it so i cant say on the rariety pre/post nerf) the fact has not been changed that this item ahs been around and there are a gazillion on the server. By paying 40k for one YOU are responsible for jacking with the market value. If no one is willing to pay insane amounts of money for the item what can a seller do? Nothing, but keep it and use it or let it rot. If they are hard up for cash they will let it go. Do not give in to overpriced items, you are not only screwing yourself but screwing over the market in general. <br>
<br>
Spells. Ok spells is a touchy issue. I play a melee (war) on main pc, and i bot a wiz-ho on my 2nd pc. I have a 55 mage, 51 rogue beside these too chars so i been around. I can say that I know first hand what spells mean to casters and what weapons/haste items mean to melee. Let me tell you THEY ARE NOT THE SAME. Similar yes, but not the same its like apples and oranges imo.<br>
<br>
I paid 3kish for CoTH for my mage back in the day and I regretted it but i needed teh damn spell what could i do ya know?. Well I didnt realize something then,  Patience > all. WIth eq evolving as it is and a expansion being released every 15months or so the prices will drop. There are very few items in the game that are truely unique. The fungi is prolly one of them (now before you say I am contradicting myself, the reason I think the fungi price should not go up is b/c there are already a gazallion out there, unlike lets say a manarobe which there is prolly less then three thousand {wild guess no numbers to back this up}). Let us remeber the times when Kunark BP/legs where the most uber items in the game for melee and, if you are really patient and bored can check allakzahem's boards on the individual kunark bp/legs and check for people's posts from long ago that said "you will never see a mylro/cobalt/be/dw bp for sale b/c they are priceless". Well low and behold, even on our gimp arsed server you see most kunark bp's for sell (cept cobalt/donal's it seems). <br>
<br>
When buying spells I personally will never pay more then 1k for a spell. EVER. I have a wiz so i realize that spells like sunstrike are rare, however I will not budge. Maybe I will never scribe the stupid spell, but so be it. I refuse to buy it for more then 1k. <br>
<br>
In conculssion of my rant, eq has is a consumer's market. The buyer has the power, the seller is subject to the needs of the market. If somoene is not selling something ot you at a reasonableprice then somoene else wil come along and do it. If you give in to the seller's wishes, the next seller of that item will ask the same if not for more. <br>
<br>
